<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-10-07T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-10-07T04:00:00-05:00" n="220" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d220">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11230: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-10-07T17:00:00+08:00">October 7, 1930—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8:35 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>90. Following sent to Legation: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“October 7, 3 p.m. U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Panay</hi> was
                                    fired upon by trench mortars from right bank of river at a point
                                    45 miles this side of Kiukiang this morning. Fire was returned
                                    with 450 rounds machine gun ammunition and seven 3-inch shells.
                                        <hi rend="italic">Panay</hi> turned and passed point of
                                    attack twice but there was no hand firing from shore. No
                                    casualties on <hi rend="italic">Panay.</hi></p>
                                <p>Military authorities continue to announce further advances of
                                    central forces in Honan. Americans state Feng Yu-hsiang is
                                    definitely abandoning Chengchow.</p>
                                <p>Repeated to Department.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>